    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Left Bank and Right Bank Bordeaux wines?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Left Bank Bordeaux (Médoc, Haut-Médoc) are predominantly Cabernet Sauvignon-based with structured tannins and cassis flavors, exemplified by estates like Lafite and Latour. Right Bank wines (Saint-Émilion, Pomerol) feature more Merlot, offering softer textures and plum-cherry notes, with famous producers like Cheval Blanc and Pétrus. The Gironde River's gravel deposits on the Left Bank favor Cabernet Sauvignon, while the Right Bank's clay-limestone soils are ideal for Merlot.</p>
