  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How long should I decant the best Bordeaux wines before serving?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Young Bordeaux (under 10 years) benefit from 2-4 hours of decanting to soften tannins and open aromatics, while mature wines (15+ years) need only 30-60 minutes to avoid over-oxidation. First Growth wines like Margaux or Mouton-Rothschild can handle extended decanting due to their concentration, but delicate older vintages should be monitored closely. Always taste periodically during decanting, as the optimal serving window varies by producer and vintage conditions.</p>
  </div>

