    <p class="text-gray-700">The biggest mistake is buying purely based on vintage reputation without considering the specific château's performance that year, as even great vintages produce disappointing wines from some estates. Many buyers also overlook proper storage provenance—premium Bordeaux loses significant value if stored poorly, especially wines over $200. Additionally, purchasing young Bordeaux without proper cellaring facilities leads to drinking wines before they reach their potential, wasting both money and the wine's true character.</p>
